Class UserDTO

java.lang.Object
it.uninsubria.dto.UserDTO
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable
public class UserDTO extends Object implements Serializable
Data Transfer Object for User information. This class is responsible for encapsulating user data to transfer between client and server. Uses public fields for direct access with minimal constructors for different use cases.
Author:
Lorenzo Radice, 753252, CO

      Default constructor. Initializes a completely empty UserDTO.

      public UserDTO(String username, String password)
      Constructor with minimal authentication information. Useful for login operations.
      Parameters:
      username - User's unique identifier
      password - User's password

    • UserDTO

      public UserDTO(String username, String password, String name, String surname, String nation, String city, String address, Double latitude, Double longitude, Date birth_date, String role)
      Constructor with all user information including nation and city. Useful for full data transfer operations.
      Parameters:
      username - User's unique identifier
      password - User's password
      name - User's first name
      surname - User's last name
      nation - User's nation of residence
      city - User's city of residence
      address - User's street address
      latitude - User's latitude location
      longitude - User's longitude location
      birth_date - User's birthdate (can be null)
      role - User's role (client/owner)

    • UserDTO

      public UserDTO(String username, String password, String name, String surname, Date birth_date, UserRoleDTO role)
      Constructor with all user information except address. Useful for operations where address is not needed.
      Parameters:
      username - User's username
      password - User's password
      name - User's first name
      surname - User's last name
      birth_date - User's birthdate (can be null)
      role - User's role (client/owner)
